OL,3,C"It was terrifying"
OL,5,FHe continued in written submissions:
OL,6,F"In a series of widely viewed videos,
OL,7,Fa print publication, as well as during
OL,8,Fin-person lectures, the defendant
OL,9,Finsisted that the terrorist attack in
OL,10,Fwhich the claimants were
OL,11,Fcatastrophically injured did not
OL,12,Fhappen and that the claimants were
OL,13,Fparticipants or 'crisis actors' in a
OL,14,Fstate-orchestrated hoax, who had
OL,15,Frepeatedly, publicly and egregiously
OL,16,Flied to the public for monetary gain."
OL,18,FMr Price had said a total of #75,000
OL,19,Ffor the pair in damages should be
OL,20,Fawarded, as well as at least 90% of
OL,21,Ftheir legal fees.
