OL,3,C"It was terrifying"
OL,5,FPaul Oakley, for Mr Hall, said in
OL,6,Fwritten submissions that #7,500 each
OL,7,Fin damages "would be appropriate",
OL,8,Fadding there was "no justification"
OL,9,Ffor aggravated damages.
OL,11,FHe told the court: "There is no
OL,12,Fallegation of malice and that is
OL,13,Freally a fundamental point as far as
OL,14,Fdamages are concerned."
OL,16,F"Some of these harassment cases can
OL,17,Fget pretty nasty, but there was no
OL,18,Fvindictiveness."
