OL,3,C"It was terrifying"
OL,5,FMr Oakley later said that a suggested
OL,6,Finjunction was too wide, describing it
OL,7,Fas "a blanket ban" on all of Mr Hall's
OL,8,Foutput, and called the Hibberts'
OL,9,Festimated costs as "jaw dropping".
OL,11,FThe barrister said: "Mr Hall's work
OL,12,Fwas 'not about' the claimants, who
OL,13,Ffeatured only minimally in the
OL,14,Fentirety of his recorded and written
OL,15,Foutput.
OL,17,F"At best, those parts of Mr Hall's
OL,18,Fworks which concern the claimants may
OL,19,Fbe redacted but no more."
